title: Selma's Table Daphne Post author Selma's Table
directions: First we must turn a butternut squash into a puree. Peel and cut the squash into chunks. Then steam or cook the chunks till soft. Put them in a blender or food processor and blend until you end up with a smooth puree. Set 1 cup aside for this recipe, use the rest for other recipes (for ideas see blogpost).
Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit/175 degrees Celsius.

Put all ingredients in a food processor and process into a smooth batter. When you're a real sweet tooth you might want to use more sugar in this recipe. 1/3 to 1/2 cup instead of the quarter cup I used.
Butter a brownie tin (9x9 inch/23x23 cm).
Pour batter into tin and bake at 350 degrees Fahrenheit/175 degrees Celsius for 25 minutes.
ingredients: 1/3 cup cacao powder (I used Dutch processed cacao)
1/4 cup date sugar (coconut blossom sugar, palm sugar and sucanat can also be used)
100 grams of butter (I used an organic butter)
1/8 teaspoon of salt (I used Himalayan salt)
